            <h2 class="text-primary">Dataset description</h2>
            <br>
            <p>The dataset collects demographic information, neuropathological information, medical history, and
                Post-mortem interval. Each
                tissue is accompanied with high resolution brain images.
            </p>
            <h4 class="text-secondary">Autopsy Type</h4>
            <p>The tissue collection covers three autopsy type: brain, brain and spinal cord, and full body.
            </p>
            <h4 class="text-secondary">Availability</h4>
            <p> Tissues are available in two storage methods: formalin fixed, and fresh frozen.</p>
            <h4 class="text-secondary">Neuropathological diagnosis
            </h4>
            <p>The collection covers a wide range of brain and nervous system diseases</p>
            <p>The brain bank collects tissue from people suffer from: </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Alzheimer’s Disease</li>
                <li>Brain Tumour</li>
                <li>Down’s Syndrome</li>
                <li>Fahr’s Disease</li>
                <li>Familial Alzheimer's Disease</li>
                <li>Frontotemporal Dementia</li>
                <li>Huntington's Disease</li>
                <li>Lewy Body Disease</li>
                <li>Multiple Sclerosis</li>
                <li>Multiple System Atrophy</li>
                <li>Neural Storage Disorder</li>
                <li>Parkinson's Disease</li>
                <li>Progressive Supranuclear Palsy</li>
                <li>Vascular Dementia</li>
            </ul>
